---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'why-you-need-it', text: 'Why You Need Insurance', level: 2 },
  { id: 'types-of-coverage', text: 'Types of Coverage', level: 2 },
  { id: 'what-to-look-for', text: 'What to Look For', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-plans', text: 'Recommended Plans', level: 2 },
  { id: 'travel-vs-expat', text: 'Travel vs Expat Insurance', level: 2 },
  { id: 'common-mistakes', text: 'Common Mistakes', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Best Digital Nomad Insurance', href: '/best/digital-nomad-insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Remote Workers', href: '/insurance-for/remote-workers' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Freelancers', href: '/insurance-for/freelancers' },
  { title: 'Portugal Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/portugal/insurance' },
  { title: 'Thailand Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/thailand/insurance' },
];

const planColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'type', header: 'Type' },
  { key: 'flexibility', header: 'Location Flexibility' },
  { key: 'price', header: 'From' },
];

const planRows = [
  { provider: 'SafetyWing', type: 'Travel Medical', flexibility: 'Very High', price: '$45/mo' },
  { provider: 'World Nomads', type: 'Travel Medical', flexibility: 'High', price: '$60/mo' },
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', type: 'Expat Health', flexibility: 'High', price: '$140/mo' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', type: 'Expat Health', flexibility: 'High', price: '$120/mo' },
  { provider: 'IMG Global', type: 'Expat Health', flexibility: 'Medium', price: '$100/mo' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Digital Nomads"
  description="Find the right health insurance as a digital nomad. Compare travel and expat plans that work when you're location-independent."
  headline="Health Insurance for Digital Nomads"
  subheadline="Coverage that works when you move often. Here's how to find the right plan for your location-independent lifestyle."
  heroImage="/images/pages/nomad-hero.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Find Nomad-Friendly Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
>
  <h2 id="why-you-need-it">Why You Need Insurance</h2>
  <p>
    As a digital nomad, you might not have access to employer health benefits or your home country's public healthcare. A serious illness or accident abroad can cost tens of thousands of dollars without insurance.
  </p>
  <p>
    Beyond emergencies, good coverage helps with:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Routine doctor visits when you're not feeling well</li>
    <li>Prescriptions you need to maintain</li>
    <li>Peace of mind while working remotely</li>
    <li>Meeting visa requirements in some countries</li>
  </ul>

  <CTABox
    title="Find Coverage That Travels"
    description="Compare plans designed for people who move between countries."
    buttonText="See My Options →"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <h2 id="types-of-coverage">Types of Coverage</h2>
  <p>
    Digital nomads typically choose between two main types of insurance:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8 not-prose">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-6">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
        <img src="/images/pages/nomad-travel-insurance.png" alt="Travel insurance" class="w-16 h-16 object-contain" />
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Travel Medical Insurance</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Designed for people constantly on the move.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-600">
        <li>Cheaper (typically $40-80/month)</li>
        <li>More flexible with destinations</li>
        <li>Focused on emergencies and acute care</li>
        <li>Limited for ongoing conditions</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-neutral-700">
        <strong>Good for:</strong> Nomads who move frequently, are young and healthy, and mainly need emergency coverage.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-xl p-6">
      <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
        <img src="/images/pages/nomad-health-insurance.png" alt="Health insurance" class="w-16 h-16 object-contain" />
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">International Health Insurance</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-3">Comprehensive coverage like regular health insurance.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-sm text-neutral-600">
        <li>More expensive ($100-250+/month)</li>
        <li>Covers routine care, checkups, prescriptions</li>
        <li>Better for chronic conditions</li>
        <li>Often accepted for visas</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-4 text-sm text-neutral-700">
        <strong>Good for:</strong> Nomads who stay in places longer, have ongoing health needs, or want comprehensive coverage.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="what-to-look-for">What to Look For</h2>
  <p>
    When evaluating plans as a digital nomad, pay attention to:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Country coverage:</strong> Does it work in all the places you plan to go?</li>
    <li><strong>Home country coverage:</strong> Are you covered when visiting home?</li>
    <li><strong>US coverage:</strong> If you're American or visit the US, this affects pricing significantly</li>
    <li><strong>Minimum stays:</strong> Some plans require you to be abroad for a minimum period</li>
    <li><strong>Pre-existing conditions:</strong> How are ongoing health issues handled?</li>
    <li><strong>Claims process:</strong> Can you file claims easily from anywhere?</li>
    <li><strong>Telemedicine:</strong> Virtual doctor access is valuable for nomads</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="recommended-plans">Recommended Plans</h2>
  <p>
    Here are plans commonly used by digital nomads, ranging from budget travel medical to comprehensive expat coverage.
  </p>

  <div class="my-8 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
    <ComparisonTable columns={planColumns} rows={planRows} />
  </div>

  <h3>Budget-Friendly Options</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>SafetyWing</strong> is popular among nomads for its low cost and flexibility. It covers emergencies and some outpatient care. It's subscription-based, so you can start and stop as needed.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>World Nomads</strong> offers similar coverage with good adventure sports options if you're into activities like surfing or hiking.
  </p>

  <h3>Comprehensive Options</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Cigna Global</strong> and <strong>Allianz Care</strong> provide fuller health coverage. These make sense if you settle in places for months at a time, have health conditions to manage, or want access to routine care.
  </p>
  <p>
    <a href="/compare/cigna-global-vs-allianz-care">Compare Cigna Global vs Allianz Care</a>
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Compare Your Options"
    description="See actual quotes based on your travel plans and needs."
    buttonText="Get My Quote →"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna-global"
  />

  <h2 id="travel-vs-expat">Travel vs Expat Insurance</h2>
  <p>
    Not sure which type you need? Here's a quick guide:
  </p>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 my-8 not-prose">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-xl p-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <img src="/images/pages/nomad-travel-insurance.png" alt="" class="w-10 h-10 object-contain" />
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900">Choose Travel Medical If:</h3>
      </div>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You move every few weeks or months</li>
        <li>You're young and healthy</li>
        <li>You mainly need emergency coverage</li>
        <li>Budget is a top priority</li>
        <li>You don't need routine care access</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-xl p-6">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <img src="/images/pages/nomad-health-insurance.png" alt="" class="w-10 h-10 object-contain" />
        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900">Choose Expat Insurance If:</h3>
      </div>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600">
        <li>You stay in places for 3+ months</li>
        <li>You have ongoing health needs</li>
        <li>You want routine care and checkups</li>
        <li>You need visa-compliant coverage</li>
        <li>Comprehensive coverage matters more than cost</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p>
    <a href="/guides/international-health-insurance-vs-travel">Read our detailed comparison of travel vs expat insurance</a>
  </p>

  <h2 id="common-mistakes">Common Mistakes</h2>
  <p>
    Avoid these pitfalls when getting insurance as a digital nomad:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Assuming travel insurance is enough:</strong> Basic travel insurance often has low limits and only covers emergencies</li>
    <li><strong>Ignoring pre-existing conditions:</strong> If you have ongoing health issues, make sure they're covered</li>
    <li><strong>Forgetting about home country visits:</strong> Some plans don't cover you when visiting home</li>
    <li><strong>Not checking visa requirements:</strong> Some countries require specific insurance types</li>
    <li><strong>Waiting until you're sick:</strong> Pre-existing condition exclusions mean you need coverage before issues arise</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <h3>Can I use my home country's insurance abroad?</h3>
  <p>
    Usually only for emergencies and with many limitations. Most domestic insurance plans don't cover routine care abroad. If you're living as a nomad, you need international coverage.
  </p>

  <h3>What about the Affordable Care Act (for Americans)?</h3>
  <p>
    The ACA individual mandate penalty is currently $0, so you're not penalized for not having US coverage. However, you'll need coverage for time spent in the US, and US-included plans cost significantly more.
  </p>

  <h3>How do claims work when I'm abroad?</h3>
  <p>
    Most plans let you pay upfront and submit claims online for reimbursement. Some have direct billing arrangements with hospitals in major cities. Telemedicine options can help with minor issues without needing a physical visit.
  </p>

  <h3>What if I settle down in one country?</h3>
  <p>
    If you stop moving and establish residence somewhere, you might consider switching to local insurance or getting a plan specifically for that country. Check our country guides for destination-specific options.
  </p>

  <CTABox
    title="Ready to Get Covered?"
    description="Compare plans that work for your nomadic lifestyle."
    buttonText="Find My Plan →"
    buttonHref="/go/cigna-global"
    variant="highlight"
  />

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance needs vary based on individual circumstances. We are not insurance brokers or licensed advisors. Always verify coverage details with insurance providers.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
